SIMPLE: enough
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enough
<hw>E*nough"</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*n⟦ucr⟧f")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>inoh</ets>, <ets>inow</ets>, <ets>enogh</ets>, AS.
<ets>gen⟦omac⟧h</ets>, <ets>gen⟦omac⟧g</ets>, a. & adv. (akin to OS.
<ets>gin⟦omac⟧g</ets>, D. <ets>genoeg</ets>, OHG. <ets>ginoug</ets>, G.
<ets>genug</ets>, Icel. <ets>gn⟦omac⟧gr</ets>, Sw. <ets>nog</ets>, Dan.
<ets>nok</ets>, Goth. <ets>gan⟦omac⟧hs</ets>), fr. <ets>geneah</ets> it
suffices (akin to Goth. <ets>ganah</ets>); pref. <ets>ge-</ets> + a root
akin to L. <ets>nancisci</ets> to get, Skr. <ets>na⟦cced⟧</ets>, Gr.
<grk>'enegkei^n</grk> to carry.]</ety> <def>Satisfying desire; giving
content; adequate to meet the want; sufficient; -- usually, and more
elegantly, following the noun to which it belongs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How many hired servants of my father's have bread
<qex>enough</qex> and to spare!</q> <rj><qau>Luke xv. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enough
<hw>E*nough"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a degree or
quantity that satisfies; to satisfaction; sufficiently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fully; quite; -- used to express slight augmentation
of the positive degree, and sometimes equivalent to <xex>very</xex>;
<as>as, he is ready <ex>enough</ex> to embrace the offer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I know you well <qex>enough</qex>; you are Signior Antonio.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou knowest well <qex>enough</qex> . . . that this is no time to
lend money.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a tolerable degree; -- used to express mere
acceptableness or acquiescence, and implying a degree or quantity rather
less than is desired; <as>as, the song was well
<ex>enough</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Enough</xex> usually follows the word it
modifies.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Enough
<hw>E*nough"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sufficiency; a quantity which
satisfies desire, is adequate to the want, or is equal to the power or
ability; <as>as, he had <ex>enough</ex> to do take care of
himself</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Enough</xex> is as good as a
feast.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And Esau said, I have <qex>enough</qex>, my brother.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xxxiii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>enough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: enough
<hw>e*nough"</hw>, <pos>interj.</pos> <def>An exclamation denoting
sufficiency, being a shortened form of <xex>it is
enough</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enounce</ent>⟦br⟧
